ui.welcome_title=Welcome to Inner World
ui.welcome_blackbg1=§rThis world is filled with magic, places to explore, quests, and GIGAAAANTIC monsters to hunt!\n\n
ui.welcome_blackbg2=§n§l<MONEY>§r To begin your journey, head to the Bank. There, you can get a small amount of §l§6Besta Coins§r §r(the local currency) to start your adventure.\n\n
ui.welcome_blackbg3=§n§l<GEARS>§r Need gear? The Blacksmith sells basic items. Stop by and check it out!\n\n
ui.welcome_blackbg4=§n§l<FOOD & SLEEP>§r Hungry or need to rest? The Tavern offers local food and a warm bed to spend the night.§r\n\n
ui.welcome_blackbg5=§n§l<CITIES>§r Well... You are now in the city of §l§nBéstamo§r! There are a total of 7 cities, each with its own infrastructure, rentable houses, temples to set your spawn point, and much more.\n\n
ui.welcome_blackbg6=§r§n§lRemember: you can manage your character through the Player's Book, which is in your inventory!\n\n

ui.motd_title=Message of the Day
ui.motd_blackbg1=Groups and experience sharing: It's really annoying to go hunting and have one or two players benefit from all the XP gained, right? Here you can create a group and share XP equally.
ui.motd_blackbg2=Experience bonus: Enjoy the daily XP bonus! Every day, you will receive a 50%%% XP gain for 2 hours in addition to the base XP from the creatures you defeat, making it easier to level up your character.
ui.motd_blackbg3=Custom shields: A great achievement for the server, as Minecraft doesn't easily allow the creation of such items. However, our shield system is much more complete and complex, requiring you to improve your PVP skills. Here, besides 'crouching' to defend yourself, you will also need to 'focus' on the target you want to defend against.
ui.motd_blackbg4=Passive Defense: Another feature found in true RPGs is passive defense, which builds your 'resistance' to attacks by reducing damage. This passive defense is possible with any equippable item such as armor, shields, and weapons, which offer a type of passive defense (visible by hovering over the item). The higher your passive defense, the more resistance you have to physical attacks. To check your total defense, go to Profile in the Adventurer's Book.
ui.motd_blackbg5=Protection Zone: If you're in danger, just run to a protected area (like temples or banks). There, creatures or even players won't be able to attack you!
ui.motd_blackbg6=\n\n§aMuch more is being developed! Enjoy and ask your questions on our Discord (discord.innerworld.live)\n\n


