## A New World! ##
##################

## NPC Settings
system.npc.cap_gregor_sharpblade.welcome=Mmm!! It's been a long time since I've eaten something hot! Hey! What are you looking for???

system.quest.0.name=A New World!
system.quest.0.description=You have started your adventure in Inner World, and there is a lot to do...

## Root button return messages
system.quest.0.msg.welcome.0=Did you say adventures?? Adventure is my middle name! I mean... it is Sharpblade, but you get the idea... I do not think I have seen you around here before, are you new in town?
system.quest.0.msg.welcome.2=So now that you are aware of §l§6Bilbobag§r§f needs, I may have another one for you.

system.quest.0.msg.in_progress=What do you mean, more adventures? You have not even followed the last tip I gave you!
system.quest.0.msg.complete=Looks like you already know every adventure I could tell you about. If I hear anything new, you can be sure I will let you know.

## Dont have required items return message
ui.quest.0.msg.not_match_required=

## Dialog messages
ui.quest.0.msg.1=Well... you should have an adventurer's book. In that book, you will write down every adventure you face. It is important to document them, and with that, you will become part of the Adventurers Guild and be able to help other newcomers!\nFor now, I have only heard of one possible adventure. The city postman officer §l§6Bilbobag§r§f is the one who needs help. He stays near the port, go look for him and see what he has to say...\n\nTake this too, you may need it.
ui.quest.0.msg.2=Well... I heard rumors about a lost tomb in the desert. I do not know the exact location, but who knows what you might find there?

## Quest log (check points)
system.quest.0.check_point.1=You have started your journey in Inner World. §l§tCaptain Gregor Sharpblade§r§j seems to have taken a liking to you and gave you a new mission. Make him proud and fill every page of this book with your greatest adventures!
system.quest.0.check_point.2=§l§tBilbobag§r§j asked for some healp, don't seems to be hard.
system.quest.0.check_point.3=§l§tCaptain Gregor Sharpblade§r§j mentioned rumors about a lost tomb in the desert. I should find the place. Who knows what riddles I might find there, or maybe... Riches...
#########################################################


#######################
## The Postman Guild ##
#######################

## NPC Settings
system.npc.magician_grinden.welcome=Hello! Welcome to my humble hideout... Oops! I mean humble residence! I am the greatest magician of all time! You must be one of my fans!\n\nCome see one of my shows someday!
system.npc.king_merkwin.welcome=Fine, you have convinced me... I will listen to you...

system.quest.1.name=The Postman Guild
system.quest.1.description=Bilbobag asked for your help with a few postman tasks, so you can eventually become a member of the Postman Guild.

## Root button return messages
system.quest.1.msg.welcome.0=Would you like to become part of the Postman Guild? Our evaluation standards are very high, but you look promising...
system.quest.1.msg.welcome.1=Ahoy, traveler... This old port brings back memories. I once crossed these waters chasing rumors, storms, and treasures that probably never existed.\n\nLost a few coins, gained a few scars, and learned one thing: the sea gives you only the adventure you are brave enough to survive.
system.quest.1.msg.welcome.2=Ah, traveler... Ras Baha’s desert route is not kind to the careless. I have crossed those sands more times than I can count, chasing mirages, lost caravans, and storms that could swallow a ship whole.\n\nI lost my fear somewhere out there... along with a good pair of boots.
system.quest.1.msg.welcome.3=Ah, traveler... The route to Honzaki teaches patience before courage. I crossed those waters under crimson skies, following lantern lights, silent waves, and winds that seemed to speak in riddles.\n\nI found no treasure there... only discipline, calm, and a blade that taught me to respect both.
system.quest.1.msg.welcome.4=Hmph... Another soft-skinned traveler staring like I bite for sport. I control the Grishnakh route, through flooded swamps, mud, rot, and things that would make your bones shake.\n\nLost a few crewmen, broke a few skulls, and learned one thing: fear sinks faster when you growl back.
system.quest.1.msg.welcome.5=Ah, traveler... The route to Edélfia begins at sea, but it is the river that tests your soul. Long waters, ancient trees, and elven lights watching from the forest mist.\n\nI once followed that river in silence and learned one thing: some paths do not need storms to feel dangerous.
system.quest.1.msg.welcome.6=Ah, traveler... The route to Terakan climbs where the sea ends and the canyon begins. A city carved into the mountains, with drums echoing through stone and a view wide enough to humble any sailor.\n\nI have seen many ports, but Terakan taught me one thing: some places are not reached by courage alone... you need strong legs too.
system.quest.1.msg.welcome.7=Hah... Murgonur is no ordinary route, traveler. That city has been drowning in chaos since demons rose during the Sacred War thousands of years ago.\n\nRed earth, burning fog, rivers of lava, and an enormous volcano watching over it all... protecting the city, or maybe waiting to finish it.
system.quest.1.msg.welcome.12=Of course it is me! I am the Spectacular Grinden! The greatest magician of all time! \n\nWhat?... You did not come to see one of my shows? A letter for me??
system.quest.1.msg.welcome.15=Come on, tell me you brought the bones. Our postman are in serious danger! Did you get them?
system.quest.1.msg.welcome.16=Now that you are an official postman, I can send you on more secret missions.\n\nOne of our members has gone missing. His name is §l§cIgnarbag§r§f, and I need someone very brave to look for him, or at least find his body... Would you be capable of such a mission?\n\nSources say he was last seen in the city of §l§cMurgonur§r§f.

system.quest.1.msg.in_progress_grinden=Ohh... Another fan looking for an autograph?
system.quest.1.msg.in_progress_king_merkwin=You have earned my respect, Non-Horn... But remember your place in my city.
system.quest.1.msg.in_progress=Remember! Inner World’s mail service depends on you!
system.quest.1.msg.complete=What a huge adventure you went through! You exceeded my expectations, and I truly appreciate your effort!\n\nBut for now I have no new adventures, come back when you need me!

## Dialog messages
ui.quest.1.msg.1=Hm, I am considering your determination, but first you will need to prove your worth by doing a few tasks for us. Your first task will be quite simple.
ui.quest.1.msg.2=Better write down the instructions, ready?\n\nYou will have to check all the routes our members travel and make sure there are no problems with them. First speak with §l§cCaptain Billfor§r§f here in Béstamo, then speak with §l§cCaptain Anen of Ras Baha§r§f, then §l§cCaptain Shao§r§f of Honzaki, after that speak with §l§cCaptain Murdrak§r§f of Grishnakh and then §l§cCaptain Fendrel§r§f of Edélfia, then go to Terakan and speak with §l§cCaptain Zayd§r§f. Finally, talk to §l§cCaptain Aleister§r§f of Murgonur.\n\nWhen you are done, come back here and report if you found any problems.
ui.quest.1.msg.3=Problems?? They usually run away from me! Tell Bilbobag everything is smooth sailing over here!
ui.quest.1.msg.4=Are you underestimating me, little one? If Bilbobag thinks I have problems on my routes, then he clearly does not know me well...\n\nTell him everything here is under control.
ui.quest.1.msg.5=This city has enjoyed many years of peace. I do not recall ever finding problems on my routes.
ui.quest.1.msg.6=Look around you... This is a swamp, do you see a problem with that?! I do not!! Now let me work!
ui.quest.1.msg.7=We live in paradise around here. If anyone has problems, it is definitely Grishnakh...
ui.quest.1.msg.8=I had a few problems on my routes to Grishnakh, but we solved them with a nice piece of rotten meat (Ugh!) and the locals. You can tell my buddy Bilbobag everything is fine here, apart from the stomachache I got!
ui.quest.1.msg.9=The only problem around here is that you are delaying my deliveries!
ui.quest.1.msg.10=Great news, great news!! Since we have no problems on our routes, I can offer you the second task.\n\nI heard that the mailbox in §l§cGrishnakh§r§f is jammed. Those devices require very special tools for maintenance, go there and try to fix it, I am sure you can do it... Our companion §l§cNargbag§r§f will be happy to get a little help.
ui.quest.1.msg.11=§2You have already fixed the mail machine!
ui.quest.1.msg.12=§2You look very strong and managed to unjam the mail machine on the first try!
ui.quest.1.msg.13=§2With determination, even though you are not that strong, you manage to unjam the mail machine!
ui.quest.1.msg.14=§cYou are not strong enough and fail miserably while trying to unjam the mailbox, keep trying...
ui.quest.1.msg.15=Good thing you managed to fix it! I thought I would have to go there myself... That place gives me the creeps...\n\nBut with this task done, I can now allow you to become part of the Postman Guild. You are now a §l§6Postman Assistant!§r§f Welcome! With this title, you may use our express delivery services!\n\nBut do not stop just yet, I have one more mission. Would you like to hear more?
ui.quest.1.msg.16=This time I need you to look for a magician called §l§cGrinden§r§f. He must be hiding in the jungles of Edélfia from his creditors. Once you find him, deliver this bill so he can pay it as soon as possible!
ui.quest.1.msg.17=A letter for me??\nI hope it is that money I borrowed... Hand it over...
ui.quest.1.msg.18=You lost the letter??? Search for it and come back when you find it, I really need that money...
ui.quest.1.msg.19=What?? You must be mistaken! My name? No, my name is not Grinden, it is Prinden....
ui.quest.1.msg.20=You found Grinden? Good, you have talent and a promising future!\n\nNow you must be eager for the next mission... Well, this one is to help us with a classic postman problem... It is called DOGS! Yes, we keep a stock of bones to pacify the situation, but it is running low.\n\nCould you collect 64 bones to refill our stock?
ui.quest.1.msg.21=Now you must be eager for the next mission... Well, this one is to help us with a classic postman problem... It is called DOGS! Yes, we keep a stock of bones to pacify the situation, but it is running low.\n\nCould you collect 64 bones to refill our stock?
ui.quest.1.msg.22=No problem, little adventurer, I fully trust that you will manage! But do not waste time, or our postmen will start looking like walking bones to those dogs!
ui.quest.1.msg.23=Very good, little adventurer. From now on, you have become an §l§6Official Postman§r§f! Congratulations!!\n\nFrom now on, you will be able to buy express chests and letters for a lower price.
ui.quest.1.msg.24=Yes, I remember seeing §l§cIgnarbag§r§f wandering around here. He was doing one of his routes, but he looked a bit worried. From what he told me, he needed to cross the zombie village to the §lnorthwest§r§f of here to reach one of his destinations. I advised him to take a longer and safer path... I have not seen him since.
ui.quest.1.msg.25=§cYou found the body of §l§6Ignarbag§r§c, the postman...
ui.quest.1.msg.26=WHAT?!?!?! That is terrible! We lost an incredible member who did many things for our guild...\nI am saddened, but I will have to inform his family...\n\nThank you, brave postman, you honored our guild. From now on, you will be able to buy express chests and letters for a lower price.\n\nYou now hold the title of §l§cHonored Postman§r§f!\n\nAccept this as a reward.
ui.quest.1.msg.27=I have one last task for you, Honored Postman. This is one I did not want to assign to you, we always lose members when we send them to this destination... \n\nWe have a letter from the mother of King §l§cMerkwin of Minovalin§r§f, and we must fulfill our duty, or our honor as the Great Postman Guild will be at stake!\n\nBut I see no one better suited than you.\n\nDo you accept this task?
ui.quest.1.msg.28=§o§l§p%1§r §l§cNo! The Non-horns have reached my city! BODYGUARDS, ATTACK!
ui.quest.1.msg.29=What!? You have a letter for me?
ui.quest.1.msg.30=My beloved mother... How I miss her... Thank you for delivering this letter. It meant a lot to me!
ui.quest.1.msg.31=§l§cDo not take them lightly! MY BODYGUARDS ARE ALWAYS READY!
ui.quest.1.msg.32=What a great adventure! You exceeded my expectations, and I truly appreciate your effort!\n\nAnd with great pleasure, I grant you the highest position in our Postman Guild, §l§cGrand Postman§r§f!\n\nFrom today onward, you have permission to travel on our cargo ships with a very attractive price. I am sending an official notice right now to all captaincies of the main cities!\n\nWelcome aboard!

## Quest log (check points)
system.quest.1.check_point.1=I have to check all the routes used by the mail ship captains and make sure there are no problems with them. First I will go to §l§tCaptain Billfor§r§j of Béstamo, then §l§tCaptain Anen§r§j of Ras Baha, then §l§tCaptain Shao§r§j of Honzaki, after that §l§tCaptain Murdrak§r§j of Grishnakh, then §l§tCaptain Fendrel§r§j of Edélfia, then to Terakan with §l§tCaptain Zayd§r§j, and finally §l§tCaptain Aleister§r§j of Murgonur.\n\nOnce I finish, I have to report back to §l§tBilbobag§r§j in Béstamo.
system.quest.1.check_point.2=Captain Billfor gave good news, but I still need to investigate §l§tCaptain Anen§r§j of Ras Baha, §l§tCaptain Shao§r§j of Honzaki, §l§tCaptain Murdrak§r§j of Grishnakh, §l§tCaptain Fendrel§r§j of Edélfia, §l§tCaptain Zayd§r§j of Terakan and §l§tCaptain Aleister§r§j of Murgonur.
system.quest.1.check_point.3=Captain Anen seems very confident about her routes, but I still need to investigate §l§tCaptain Shao§r§j of Honzaki, §l§tCaptain Murdrak§r§j of Grishnakh, §l§tCaptain Fendrel§r§j of Edélfia, §l§tCaptain Zayd§r§j of Terakan and §l§tCaptain Aleister§r§j of Murgonur.
system.quest.1.check_point.4=Captain Shao said he lives in a world of peace, but I still need to investigate §l§tCaptain Murdrak§r§j of Grishnakh, §l§tCaptain Fendrel§r§j of Edélfia, §l§tCaptain Zayd§r§j of Terakan and §l§tCaptain Aleister§r§j of Murgonur.
system.quest.1.check_point.5=Captain Murdrak seems relieved to live in a swamp, but I still need to investigate §l§tCaptain Fendrel§r§j of Edélfia, §l§tCaptain Zayd§r§j of Terakan and §l§tCaptain Aleister§r§j of Murgonur.
system.quest.1.check_point.6=Captain Fendrel does not seem to like swamps very much, despite reporting that everything is fine on his routes, but I still need to investigate §l§tCaptain Zayd§r§j of Terakan and §l§tCaptain Aleister§r§j of Murgonur.
system.quest.1.check_point.7=Rotten meat? Well... Must be some kind of local cuisine, at least that is how Captain Zayd made it sound, but I still need to investigate §l§tCaptain Aleister§r§j of Murgonur.
system.quest.1.check_point.8=Yeah... Captain Aleister seems a bit grumpy, but he also seems to handle his own problems...\nNow it is time to return with the news to §l§tBilbobag§r§j in Béstamo.
system.quest.1.check_point.9=Bilbobag trusted my cleverness to fix a mailbox in §l§tGrishnakh§r§j with this special tool. I will use the tool on the mailbox to repair it.
system.quest.1.check_point.10=Mailbox fixed! Now I will go back and report to §l§tBilbobag§r§j in Béstamo.
system.quest.1.check_point.11=Now that Grishnakh's mailbox is fixed, I earned Bilbobag's trust and was promoted to §l§tPostman Assistant§r§j. With this, I can now send letters through the mail service.
system.quest.1.check_point.12=It seems that the §l§tSpectacular Grinden§r§j has disappeared, and his mail is not being delivered. I need to locate him in §l§tEdélfia§r§j and deliver the envelope to him.
system.quest.1.check_point.13=The Spectacular Grinden did not want to receive this letter, but my job is done. Now I will report back to §l§tBilbobag§r§j in Béstamo.
system.quest.1.check_point.14=§l§tBilbobag§r§j in Béstamo was happy that I found the Spectacular Grinden. I am ready for the next mission.
system.quest.1.check_point.15=It sounds like a joke, but the postmen are running out of bones, a vital tool for their work to continue without the risk of... bites... I need to deliver 64 bones to §l§tBilbobag§r§j in Béstamo.
system.quest.1.check_point.16=After delivering the bones to Bilbobag, he promoted me to §l§tOfficial Postman§r§j, allowing me to travel for less on the mail ships.
system.quest.1.check_point.17=With my promotion to §l§tOfficial Postman§r§j, aside from paying less for the exchange services, new responsibilities came along, and an ultra-secret mission was revealed to me. I need to start searching for the missing postman §l§tIgnarbag§r§j. He used to work the routes of §l§tMurgonur§r§j, maybe I can start there.
system.quest.1.check_point.18=I found the body of §l§tIgnarbag§r§j. It was not what they wanted to find, but it was already expected... Unfortunately, I will have to bring the terrible news to §l§tBilbobag§r§j in Béstamo.
system.quest.1.check_point.19=After reporting the sad news to Bilbobag, I was recognized for my bravery in facing the city of Murgonur and was promoted to §l§tHonored Postman§r§j. Maybe more missions await me with §l§tBilbobag§r§j in Béstamo.
system.quest.1.check_point.20=This seems to be my final mission... From what I heard, Minovalin is a very dangerous place. It lies to the §l§tSOUTH§r§j of Béstamo, inside a cave that is easy to spot from a distance, but heavily protected...
system.quest.1.check_point.21=What a challenge this minotaur king gave me! It is hard to convince him, but I still need to deliver the letter.
system.quest.1.check_point.22=The letter to King Merkwin was delivered! Phew... That was close... Now I have to report back to §l§tBilbobag§r§j in Béstamo.
system.quest.1.check_point.23=After all this adventure, all that is left for me is to enjoy cheaper trips with the postman fleet as a §l§tGrand Postman§r§j!
